SUMMARY:Wargames - Java vulnerabilities and why you should care
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20240606T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20240606T210000
UID:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/301350591/@community-events
DESCRIPTION:🔗 https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/301350591/\n
 📍 ENSEIRB\, 1 Avenue du Docteur Albert Schweitzer\, Talence\, France\n\
 n**Java is great** and we all spend time on making it more performant\, mo
 re scalable and maintainable.\nBut we better should also spend some time o
 n making it more secure.\nWith all that new Java releases and features als
 o come **new vulnerabilities and exploits**. Because Java is everywhere\, 
 it has a huge attack surface which makes it interesting for hackers to sea
 rch for vulnerabilities in Java and foremost in Java based applications.\n
 I'm not a Java security specialist and if you are like me wonder what all 
 these mystique acronyms like NVD\, CVE\, CVSS\, CPU\, PSU etc. **mean and 
 how they are related to Java security\,** come to this session and I will 
 explain it to you. It will also be shown what tools are available to you t
 o check whether your Java application is vulnerable to known issues\n\nCom
 munauté: bordeauxjug
LOCATION:ENSEIRB\, 1 Avenue du Docteur Albert Schweitzer\, Talence\, Franc
 e
TZID:Europe/Paris
URL:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/301350591/
